      "risk": "Pinned memory (mlock) for key cache limits scalability. Each cached DEK consumes non-swappable memory. With many customers/keys, memory pressure becomes an issue.",
      "severity": "medium",
      "mitigation": "1) Limit cache size to active keys only (LRU eviction). 2) DEKs are small (~32 bytes each) — 10,000 keys = ~320KB pinned. 3) Set ulimit for mlock appropriately. 4) Monitor pinned memory usage."
