      "src/rotation/orchestrator.{rs|go} — Background key rotation with distributed locking",
      "src/rotation/migrator.{rs|go} — Batch re-encryption of stored data"
    ],
    "patterns_to_follow": "Envelope encryption is non-negotiable. Use dependency injection for KMS adapters and audit sinks. All crypto operations must be in-process (no network calls on the hot path). Audit events are value objects — immutable, append-only. Key version is embedded in every ciphertext envelope header — readers are self-describing. Circuit breaker state transitions must be logged.",
    "pitfalls_to_avoid": [
